  "title": "Autodidacts Newsletter #26",
  "summary": "Twenty-four new posts to hitch your mind to",
  "content": "<p>We’ve been distracted these past few months by getting certified as wildland firefighters, learning to drive excavators, competing in running races, and suffering from technological breakdowns. Now, these activities have abated, allowing us to spend enough time staring into space to produce another batch of articles.</p><p>These articles are still part of <a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/100daystooffload/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">#100DaysToOffload</a>, but a few of them are more in-depth.</p><p>My favourites are probably <a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/curators-skim/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>Curation and Its Side Effects</em></a> and <a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/treat-people-as-flowers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>Treat People as Flowers</em></a>. </p><p>Runners up: my list of <a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/underrated-reasons-to-dislike-ai/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">petty (and not so petty) grievances with AI</a>, and the story of my lifelong, Sisyphean struggle with <a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/bookworm-pronunciation-syndrome/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">bookworm pronunciation syndrome</a>. There are several others that I really enjoyed writing, which I’ll let you discover for yourself.</p><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/underrated-reasons-to-dislike-ai/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Underrated reasons to dislike AI</div><div>The big arguments for and against AI have been endlessly discussed, and I don’t feel I have much to add. AGI and existential risk; human obsolescence; power use; cybersecurity; safety + censorship; slop; misinformation. Also, I’m kind of tired of everything being about AI, which is why I have</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-2c1e3235-6a96-426a-a41a-100a3bff1668.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/qwen3-vl-handwriting-ai-ocr-quality-326ab966-1979-44ef-8c9e-223276fc69d9.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/how-to-find-contact-information-of-public-figures/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>How I find the email addresses of public figures 🔒</div><div>This post is for paid members only</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-13-43-18-The-Autodidacts-de2692a687b3e982ca8ead15069bf9f73dcca58b30d9d9f737b6c9eb1cd96724.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/indie-blog-directory-directory/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>An indie blog’s directory of indie blog directories</div><div>Blogs are back. RSS is cool again. (Said the blogger to his RSS feed.) Here is a collection of small, independent directories of blogs, personal websites, and smol/indie/slow/human web sites that I’ve run across and bookmarked. Most of them accept submissions. Some of them have RSS</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/escher_stairs-c689b3ebb72399f7252031ab5a39f9e5d33003584d2e8a8a01c5f8f695d293f2.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/ideas-evolve-in-dialogue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Ideas Evolve in Dialogue</div><div>You can sort of have a conversation with a book. I sometimes write rude comments in the margins when I disagree with the author. But the Stoics recommend that when you’re insulted, you just ignore it. Books are incredibly advanced stoics in this regard. And it’s kind of</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Holbein-_Hans_-_Desiderius_Erasmus_-_Kunstmuseum_Basel-1000px-70bea2a4a332d8afb88616ea8cfe28a557cf4bfa42b083f38ee8e24aa27477a2.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/old-site-new-site-bookmarklets/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Old site, new site bookmarklets</div><div>A small utility that’s surprisingly useful during website migrations</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-13-43-18-The-Autodidacts-de2692a687b3e982ca8ead15069bf9f73dcca58b30d9d9f737b6c9eb1cd96724.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/bookworm-pronunciation-syndrome/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Sheep Music &amp; Wedding Bands</div><div>On knowledge gaps and bookworm pronunciation syndrome</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Reuter-_Paul_Julius_von-_Nadar-_Gallica-b34370dacc3c9f180b4fc4eac2ba82c543eac03c6dcd33ec24e029318498ee0b.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/thoughts-on-digital-fragility/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Some thoughts about backing up, which occurred to me after my laptop abruptly expired</div><div>I had other plans for what to write about, and also plans for the day that didn’t involve disassembling my connection to the outside world with a screwdriver</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-13-43-18-The-Autodidacts-de2692a687b3e982ca8ead15069bf9f73dcca58b30d9d9f737b6c9eb1cd96724.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/my-criteria-for-a-good-linux-developer-laptop/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>My criteria for a good Linux developer laptop</div><div>Well-built, cheap, and fast: I pick all three.</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-97e78deb-acaa-4da9-a085-0eea4e97cb6a.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/framework-16-98323d34-02c5-4747-b56e-e350864b2d1a.webp\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/the-butterfly-effect-of-revenge-bedtime-procrastination/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>The butterfly effect of revenge bedtime procrastination</div><div>Wasting time isn’t bad because it wastes time</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-a4a1b73d-562d-41af-9530-0f6f225605ad.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Eduard_von_Gr--tzner_Studierender_M--nch_1890-d78762f1-c0e4-4bb5-b44d-71846affcf86.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/curators-skim/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Curation and its side effects</div><div>Some fundamentals about how it works, and what to do when it doesn’t</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/service-pnp-fsa-8c34000-8c34700-8c34729v-9b966a6db3da178cf5aa535588bd141bc76ef0ea4a18999dda3c1ce12307c220.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/bothering-to-understand/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Bothering to understand</div><div>First it makes you slow, then it makes you fast (maybe)</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-6edcb250-06db-4d6a-8d09-aa607fb5d842.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Feynman_lecture_1964_-10481714045--067651d4-fcdc-4987-9217-36169878541b.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/sneaking-up-on-your-goals/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Delusional Optimism &amp; the Art of Sneaking Up on Your Goals</div><div>You can succeed, but you can’t fail — because you aren’t officially trying</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/photo-1637904111135-1339365de61a-c387ec9e9b4d81b711b6a6c8f02625269c2cd03da83f58c7035e9d069f71c82f\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/the-art-of-getting-back-on-one-s-horse/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>The art of getting back on one’s horse</div><div>It’s a long process</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-3b9dc757-6414-48b3-87ba-7fa01898a253.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Weiss-Paul---s-Horse-Herman-Pl.10-b3494653-c560-4297-b149-6517ee1c4d53.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/the-bid-ask-spread-on-used-physical-goods/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>The bid-ask spread on used physical goods</div><div>For most of my life I fundamentally misunderstood buy &amp; sell prices</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-a433cff8-a6a2-42ed-ad9a-48020a6a854f.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Order_book_depth_chart-optimized-391aa873-82bf-477c-a4dc-85404680cbcd.gif\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/polymarket-temperature-markets-dissappear/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>All Polymarket temperature markets missing, along with the money bet on them</div><div>Along with the money bet on them?</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Screenshot-2026-05-18-at-11-51-21-Polymarket-The-World-s-Largest-Prediction-Market----bb69166265d84cd5bc4e7b28c985ee74117b560191e1aa297fee7fc58d9ca14e.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/how-to-drain-pasta-without-a-colander-without-burning-yourself/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>How to drain pasta without a colander, without burning yourself</div><div>A cooking tip for unusually bright cave people</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/wind-1295105_1280-7b0e999d6a9204b79ce755518699c87cd12935e079d0407d106cfae9efcbf63d.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/20-years-of-linux-and-i-finally-started-using-job-control/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>20 years of Linux and I finally started using job control</div><div>And it’s amazing</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-13-43-18-The-Autodidacts-de2692a687b3e982ca8ead15069bf9f73dcca58b30d9d9f737b6c9eb1cd96724.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/backpack-activation-energy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Backpack Activation Energy</div><div>Portrait of a gumption trap</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-593b54eb-0b43-4f28-9ca1-a51dcc50d765.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Mali_-_local_transport-16d274d7-9a27-46c0-8cec-d9eea0191d2d.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/copy-ghost-post-id-to-clipboard-bookmarklet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Bookmarklet: Copy Ghost Post ID to Clipboard</div><div>Save several milliseconds with two lines of JavaScript</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-f363d90b2aa079b3e3ab325da7dc02ac8c47f95abcc19608a5a5924ecd961af0.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Screenshot-2025-11-27-at-13-43-18-The-Autodidacts-de2692a687b3e982ca8ead15069bf9f73dcca58b30d9d9f737b6c9eb1cd96724.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/good-offline-linux-dictionaries/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>The search for a good offline dictionary for Linux</div><div>… proved longer than expected</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-639070e6-493d-4e97-adc9-a83f52c5a1a8.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/goldendict-wordnet-e522233b-818a-4ebb-b1b0-9b508711f9c8.png\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/treat-people-as-flowers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Treat People as Flowers</div><div>Sometimes people say goodnight by saying, see you in the morning, if that’s expected. This bugs me.[1] While I certainly hope to see them in the morning, and consider it highly probable, even in a modern world, it isn’t guaranteed. To me, all goodbyes are an acknowledgement</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-d3a62cf2-597c-4b9d-abf8-ea424c37ea44.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/Poppies_bouquet_2017_G1-00ca0f9b-5a7a-4580-8eed-8d06a095524c.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/aigents/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>Let’s call ’em “aigents”</div><div>The portmanteau is overdue</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-85b0fd2d-b7c2-4570-96ba-bc7e9238f71d.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/tumblr_njf3a6rFpO1tm6vq4o1_1280-a8cecd4a-adc8-4d1c-b3e3-f290fe170cb5.jpg\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/how-to-fit-qwen3-6-35b-a3b-into-16gb-vram-run-with-llama-cpp-rtx-3080/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>How to fit Qwen 3.6 35B A3B into 16GB of VRAM, &amp; run it with Llama.cpp on an RTX 3080</div><div>The belly hangs over the belt, but it fits</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-0a303429-cda1-4045-9c46-867f2b846e2c.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/llama-cpp-llama-server-web-ui-qwen-3-6-35b-a3b-572bb6d3-44f4-45c3-aba4-14932fdf5240.gif\"></div></a></figure><figure><a href=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/holistic-optimization/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div><div>What Should We Optimize Away?</div><div>Optimize away optimizing away</div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/icon/autodidacts-logo-small-6240c6b8-54fa-4ac7-ba68-4743b28f202a.png\"><span>The Autodidacts</span><span>Curiositry</span></div></div><div><img src=\"https://www.autodidacts.io/content/images/thumbnail/cutting-firewood-at-side-camp-in-magalloway-township-maine-orig-9ebd771d-11f8-42a9-898d-0e92e81828e4.jpg\"></div></a></figure><p>Thanks for reading — some of you, for over a decade!</p><p>The Autodidacts</p>",
